{{Catalan language}}

'''Old Catalan''' was the [[Romance languages|Romance variety]] spoken in territories that spanned roughly the territories of the [[Principality of Catalonia]], the [[Kingdom of Valencia]], the [[Balearic Islands]], and the island of [[Sardinia]]; all of them then part of the [[Crown of Aragon]].

Old Catalan, classified as an Occitano Romance variety, is grouped with Old Occitan or Provençal.

