====Laterals====
It is believed that Old Catalan had two lateral palatal phonemes. The first,{{IPA|/ʎ/}}, was written as {{angle bracket|ll}} and has remained unchanged until recently. The second, reconstructed as {{IPA|/jl/}}, came from the Latin groups C'L, G'L, LE, and LI; it was written as {{angle bracket|yl}} and {{angle bracket|il}}. {{IPA|/jl/}} never appeared in initial position. This second phoneme has either merged into {{IPA|/ʎ/}} in most dialects but into {{IPA|/j/}} in a few dialects.<ref>{{cite book|last=Rasico|first=Philip|title=Estudis sobre la fonologia del català preliterari|year=1982|publisher=Curial/Publicacions de l’Abadia de Montserrat|page=194}}</ref>

Around the 12th century, word-initial {{IPA|/l/}} became {{IPA|/ʎ/}}, even though it continued to be spelled as {{angle bracket|l}} until the 15th century.{{sfn|Moll|1993|p=93}}

====Labiodentals====
{{IPA|/v/}} began to merge into {{IPA|/b/}} in some dialects around the 14th century, a process called [[betacism]].{{sfn|Recasens|1991|p=196}} Now, the distinction is maintained only in Valencia, the Balearic Islands, and southern Tarragona.{{citation needed|date=November 2015}}

===Vowels===
