The '''Sori-Harengan language''' is a [[West Manus languages|West Manus language]] spoken by approximately 570 people on the [[Sori Island|Sori]] and [[Harengan Island]]s, northwest off the coast of [[Manus Island]], and on the northwestern coast Manus Island, [[Papua New Guinea]].<ref name=e18/> It has [[subject–verb–object|SVO word order]].
